# ${args.classname}

This module provides a Kubernetes application deployment for ${args.classname}.

## Quick Start

### Using HeroScript

```hero
!!${args.name}.configure
    name: 'default'

!!${args.name}.install reset:false
```

### Using V Code

```v
import incubaid.herolib.k8_apps.${args.name}

fn main() {
@if args.singleton
    // Get the singleton instance
    mut obj := ${args.name}.get()!
@else
    // Create a new instance
    mut obj := ${args.name}.new(name: 'myinstance')!
    
    // Or get an existing instance
    // mut obj := ${args.name}.get(name: 'myinstance')!
@end

    // Deploy to Kubernetes
    obj.install()!
    
    // Check if deployed
    if installed()! {
        println('${args.classname} is deployed')
    }
    
    // Remove deployment
    obj.destroy()!
}
```

## Configuration

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `name` | string | 'default' | Instance name |
| `deployment_path` | string | '/tmp/${args.name}/deployment.yaml' | Path to generated YAML |

## API Reference

### Factory Functions

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
@if args.singleton
| `get()` | Get the singleton instance |
@else
| `new(name, create)` | Create or get an instance |
| `get(name)` | Get an existing instance |
| `set(obj)` | Store an instance |
| `exists(name)` | Check if instance exists |
| `list()` | List all instances |
| `delete(name)` | Delete an instance |
@end
| `play(heroscript)` | Execute HeroScript |
| `heroscript_loads(script)` | Load config from HeroScript |

### Lifecycle Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `install()` | Deploy to Kubernetes cluster |
| `installed()` | Check if deployed |
| `destroy()` | Remove from Kubernetes cluster |

## HeroScript Actions

| Action | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `!!${args.name}.configure` | Configure instance |
| `!!${args.name}.install` | Deploy to Kubernetes |
| `!!${args.name}.destroy` | Remove deployment |

## Templates

Kubernetes YAML manifests are in the `templates/` directory:
- `deployment.yaml` - Main deployment manifest

## Testing

Run the module tests:

```bash
v test lib/k8_apps/${args.name}/
```

### Testing Best Practice

Create a `.vsh` example script to test your module interactively:

1. Create the example directory:
   ```bash
   mkdir -p examples/k8_apps/${args.name}
   ```

2. Create `examples/k8_apps/${args.name}/${args.name}.vsh`:
   ```v
   #!/usr/bin/env -S v -n -w -gc none -cc tcc -d use_openssl -enable-globals run

   import ${args.module_path}

   mut app := ${args.name}.get(create: true)!

   app.install()!
   app.destroy()!
   ```

3. Run the example:
   ```bash
   examples/k8_apps/${args.name}/${args.name}.vsh
   ```
